On April 7, 2026, Upstate Web Co officially went live.

It's been a journey getting here. What started as a simple idea — help small businesses build a real online presence — has turned into something I'm genuinely proud of. Not because it's perfect, but because it works. And it's only the beginning.

## What We Do

We build custom websites, online stores, and web applications for small businesses and solopreneurs. That's it. No templates, no page builders, no monthly fees for sites you don't actually own.

Every project is hand-built with modern tools. Your site loads fast, ranks well on Google, and belongs to you — code, content, domain, everything. If you ever want to leave, you take it all with you.

Here's a quick look at what we offer:

- **Business Websites** — multi-page sites with CMS, blog, and payment integration. For restaurants, salons, contractors, professional services.
- **Online Stores** — product catalogs, shopping carts, checkout. For boutiques, artisan goods, specialty food, retail.
- **Custom Apps** — booking platforms, dashboards, member portals, productivity tools. For businesses that need something built specifically for how they operate.

We've already built for barbershops, women's boutiques, fitness studios, personal chefs, landscapers, and more. Every one of those projects taught us something, and every lesson made the next one better.

## How We Work

Our process is straightforward: Discovery, Proposal, Build, Review, Launch. Fixed pricing. No surprises. From first conversation to live site in as little as two weeks for a standard website, longer for apps depending on scope.

But what makes UWC different isn't the process — it's how we build.

## Agentic Coding and Governance

I use something called agentic coding. In simple terms, I've trained AI agents to help me build websites and applications. They assist with development, write content, and even help evaluate the quality of what we deliver.

Every project goes through what we call an agent governance review. It's a structured evaluation where specialized agents check the project from different angles — client expectations, end-user experience, technical quality, and strategic fit. It's not about replacing human judgment. It's about having multiple perspectives look at the work before it reaches you.

The result is faster delivery, more thorough quality checks, and a level of attention to detail that would be hard to achieve alone. I still make every final decision, but the agents make sure I'm not missing anything.

## What Powers UWC

We're proud of the companies and tools we work alongside:

- **Anthropic** powers our AI — from the development agents to the chat assistants on our sites
- **Cloudflare** handles hosting, security, and makes sure everything loads fast across the globe
- **Stripe** processes all payments and invoicing
- **Google** handles authentication for our client portal
- **Resend** delivers transactional emails and confirmations

These aren't just tools we picked off a list. Each one was chosen because it does its job exceptionally well. When you work with UWC, you benefit from all of them working together.

## What to Expect

If you're a small business owner or solopreneur thinking about your online presence, here's what working with us looks like:

1. **Start a conversation.** Visit our [Get Started](/get-started) page. You can fill out the form or just chat with our AI intake assistant — tell it about your business and it'll help figure out what you need.

2. **Get a recommendation.** Within one business day, we'll come back with a plan and a fixed-price quote. No back-and-forth negotiation.

3. **Watch it come together.** You'll get preview links as we build, and a client portal where you can track progress, review invoices, ask questions, and communicate with us directly.

4. **Launch with confidence.** Every project goes through our governance review before handoff. You get a site that's fast, tested, and genuinely yours.

## Looking Forward

We're a young company — launched on April 7th. But the work is already real. The clients are real. The portfolio is growing.

What excites me most isn't where we are. It's where this goes. Better tools, deeper partnerships, more small businesses with an online presence they're proud of. That's the vision.

If you have questions about UWC, how we work, or what we can build — visit the [About](/about) page and ask our chat assistant. It knows the story, the tools, the team. It's there to help.

And if you're ready to start something, [let's talk](/get-started).

Here's to day one.

— Josh
